# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LFA Investment OS — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development and set the values from
# your Supabase project (Project Settings → API).
#
# IMPORTANT
# - When NONE of these are set, the app runs in DEMO MODE with mock data only
#   (no authentication required). This is the default for local exploration.
# - When the two NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are set, the app switches to SECURE MODE:
#   authentication is required and data is read from Supabase under row-level
#   security.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Public — safe to expose to the browser. These identify your project and are
# protected by Row-Level Security. Without RLS these would NOT be safe; with RLS
# enabled (see supabase/migrations) the anon key only grants the access your
# policies allow.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# SECRET — server-side ONLY. The service-role key BYPASSES Row-Level Security and
# can read/write every client's data. It must NEVER be imported into a client
# component, exposed to the browser, or prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
#
# It is optional: the app does not require it for normal operation. Only set it
# if you add server-side admin tooling (e.g. seeding, audits). Leave blank
# otherwise. In Vercel, add it as an un-prefixed, encrypted environment variable.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
